author: felixk
msg: Set current version in namespace. ATM there is no easy way to find out to which version the file belongs. There are already many different versions of these configuration files all having the same version in the namespace (...). Having the version not only in the jars file name but also in the file itself can make life easier.
To see also in conjunction with DIRSTUDIO-387.
To me it looks ATM like this namespace isn't used anywhere, so the change shouldn't cause any problems - at least all integration tests have passed.
